                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Hey, those are mine! Those two issues (and this one: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;randomascii.wordpress.com&#x2F;2018&#x2F;02&#x2F;11&#x2F;zombie-processes-are-eating-your-memory&#x2F;" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;randomascii.wordpress.com&#x2F;2018&#x2F;02&#x2F;11&#x2F;zombie-processe...</a>) are equally problematic with clang. Two of them were problems with Windows, and one was a flaw in a Microsoft system management component.<p>Luckily they are all mitigated, fixed, or being fixed, so my Chrome builds run much more smoothly now.<span>
