                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Clang 7 documentation has a section on MSVC compatibility, <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;clang.llvm.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;MSVCCompatibility.html" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;clang.llvm.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;MSVCCompatibility.html</a><p>From that document:<p>Asynchronous Exceptions (SEH): Partial. Structured exceptions (__try &#x2F; __except &#x2F; __finally) mostly work on x86 and x64. LLVM does not model asynchronous exceptions, so it is currently impossible to catch an asynchronous exception generated in the same frame as the catching __try.<span>
